                    <span>I found this book to be an excellent reference for state-of-the-art vertex and pixel shaders. It's well organized, and contains many useful solutions for game developers.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Shader Programming is the Future</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
                      /
                      <span>0</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2002-09-13</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>If you want to start shader programming or if you have still some experience in shader programming this book is for you.<BR>The stuff presented here is absolutely cutting-edge. I can't understand other reviewers, who complain about the usage of ps.1.4. All the upcoming graphics cards will support ps.1.4, so it is good to get some of the examples in ps.1.4.<BR>I heard that the first print of this book was sold out after one week ... I know why !</span>
                  
              
